
** Commands

  - *.* switches to the command mode
  - *,* prefix (means all)

  - *a* append
  - *c* change
  - *d* delete line
  - *i* insert

  - *p* print
  - *l* list
  - *n* enumerate

  - *e <name>* edit and set file NAME
  - *f <name>* set file NAME
  - *w <name>* write file NAME
  - *q/Q* quit
  - *g/string/* search 
  - *s/old/new* substitute
  - *m* move line
  - *h* print last warning

** Line Addressing

  - *,* first through last line
  - *;* current to last line
  - *.* current line
  - *-[N]* from current
  - *+[N]* from current
  - */RE/* next
  - *?RE?* prev
